      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/54/15",
      "text": [
        " : «إِنِ اُضْطُرَّ اَلْمُحْرِمُ إِلَى أَنْ يَلْبَسَ قَبَاءً مِنْ بَرْدٍ وَ لاَ يَجِدُ ثَوْباً غَيْرَهُ فَلْيَلْبَسْهُ مَقْلُوباً وَ لاَ يُدْخِلْ يَدَيْهِ فِي يَدَيِ اَلْقَبَاءِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2608 - Al-Qasim ibn Muhammad al-Jawhari narrated from Ali ibn Abi Hamzah, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"If a Muhrim is compelled to wear a cloak (qabā’) made of striped cloth and cannot find any other garment, he may wear it inside out and should not insert his arms into the sleeves of the cloak.\""
        ]
      }
    },
